<!-- ─── PERFORMANCE ───────────────────────────────── -->
<section class="cs-section" style="background:#fff;" id="performance">
  <div class="cs-inner">
    <p class="section-tag fade-in">Performance</p>
    <h2 class="tech-heading fade-in delay-1">Optimisations.</h2>

    <div class="fade-in delay-2">
      <h3 class="cs-h3">WebGL via Deck.gl</h3>
      <p class="cs-desc">Deck.gl is a WebGL-powered library that leverages GPU acceleration for significantly faster rendering and smoother interactivity, enabling Crust Central to handle thousands of map pins worldwide while maintaining smooth movement and scrolling.</p>

      <h3 class="cs-h3">Image Pipeline</h3>
      <ul class="cs-bullets">
        <li><strong>CDN Delivery:</strong> Cloudinary provides low-latency image delivery worldwide.</li>
        <li><strong>Auto-optimisation:</strong> Images are compressed, converted to WebP, resized to 1000px maximum, and watermarked on upload.</li>
        <li><strong>Thumbnails:</strong> 200&times;200px thumbnails are auto-generated for fast-loading map pin previews.</li>
        <li><strong>Lazy loading:</strong> IntersectionObserver API + Next.js Image component reduce initial page load.</li>
        <li><strong>SVG icons:</strong> Lightweight, scalable, no HTTP requests.</li>
        <li><strong>Service Worker:</strong> Caches images in the browser cache API to reduce repeat requests.</li>
      </ul>

      <h3 class="cs-h3">Grid-Based Data Fetching</h3>
      <p class="cs-desc" style="margin-bottom:1rem;">Crust Central uses a grid-based system for data fetching, where each grid square has a unique ID based on coordinates. On initial load, two concurrent requests are made:</p>
      <ul class="cs-bullets" style="margin-bottom:1.5rem;">
        <li>Fetch shallow spot data worldwide &mdash; enough for map pins and thumbnails. Paginated if &gt;5,000 spots (~1MB). Browsing and filtering is near-instantaneous once complete.</li>
        <li>Pre-fetch complete spot data for grid squares surrounding the visible area. Grid IDs, timestamps, and cache depth are stored in IndexedDB to prevent duplicate requests.</li>
      </ul>
      <div class="cs-img-block">
        <img src="/assets/spot-hub/fetching-2.jpg" alt="Grid-based pre-fetching visualisation">
      </div>
      <p class="cs-desc" style="margin-bottom:1rem;">As the user moves around the map, new grid squares are cross-referenced with shallow data to determine which ones contain spots before making database requests.</p>
      <div class="cs-img-block">
        <img src="/assets/spot-hub/fetching-3.jpg" alt="Dynamic grid fetching visualisation">
      </div>

      <h3 class="cs-h3">Local-First Caching Strategy</h3>
      <div class="cs-img-block">
        <img src="/assets/spot-hub/caching.png" alt="Crust Central caching strategy diagram">
      </div>
      <p class="cs-desc" style="margin-bottom:0.8rem;">The flow for fetching spot data:</p>
      <ul class="cs-bullets">
        <li>Check IndexedDB &rarr; if found and not stale, return data</li>
        <li>Call Server Action (running on Netlify Edge)</li>
        <li>Check Redis cache &rarr; if found and not stale, return data</li>
        <li>HTTP fetch to Supabase &rarr; edge server checks in-memory cache first</li>
        <li>Request made to Supabase as final fallback</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ─── USER EXPERIENCE ───────────────────────────── -->
<section class="cs-section" id="user-experience">
  <div class="cs-inner">
